Name: Yosemite
description: Known for its granite cliffs and massive waterfalls

Name: Joshua Tree
description: Home to the Joshua Tree! Named by Mormon settlers as the tree's unique shape reminded them of a Biblical story in which Joshua reaches his hands up to the sky in prayer.

Name: The Grand Canyon
description: Most spectacular gorge in the world! Carved by the Colorado River with its layers containing records of billions of years of history.

Name: Sequoia National Park
description: Home to the giant sequoias and famous General Sherman tree. General Sherman is the largest known living single-stem tree on Earth by volume.

Name: Denali National Park
description: Highest mountain in North America. Formerly known as Mt. McKinley after an Ohio Senator who had never visited Alaska.

Name: Death Valley
description: World's hottest temperature average on Earth and high temperature of 57 °C

Name: Yellow Stone
description: Known for its geyser's and world famous Old Faithful
